commentTextItems.html: flicked just behind square to win the match

commentPostTextItems.html: So Pakistan win a memorable game of cricket by two wickets.
Ireland seemed to have the upper hand when they reduced their opponenets to 133 for 7 but superb hitting by Kamran Akmal and Wahab Riaz changed the game.
The Pakistan wicketkeeper takes the man of the match award while Kevin O'Brien takes the man of the series award.
With this victory Pakistan take the series 1-0 which will count as good preperation for their Champions Trophy campaign beginning next month.
Ger Siggins' report will be up shortly so do check that out but from Conor Hayes in a sun soaked Clontarf it's goodbye.

milestones.description: Kevin O'Brien has broken the record for most catches (33) in ODIs for IRE, going past Porterfield's 30
Paul Stirling has scored 5 hundreds in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Porterfield's record

stories.seoTitle: Ger Siggins: Ireland yearn for Test recognition
stories.summary: The top Associate team have big ambitions of playing five-day cricket, but without a clear pathway to the next level, their players are growing frustrated

stories.title: Narrow loss "heartbreaking" - Porterfield
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Pakistan, 2nd ODI, Dublin
stories.seoTitle: William Porterfield admits loss to be "heartbreaking"
stories.summary: Ireland captain William Porterfield said his side felt "disappointed" after their hopes for a maiden series win over a Test nation were quashed as Pakistan won 1-0.

stories.title: Kamran, Wahab dash Irish hopes
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Pakistan, 2nd ODI, Dublin
stories.seoTitle: Kamran Akmal, Wahab Riaz dash Irish hopes
